LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 415
BY WAYS AND MEANS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO ENERGY INFRASTRUCTURE; PROVIDING LEGISLATIVE INTENT; AMENDING
3 CHAPTER 3, TITLE 61, IDAHO CODE, BY THE ADDITION OF A NEW SECTION 61-338,
4 IDAHO CODE, TO ESTABLISH PROVISIONS REGARDING RESTRICTIONS ON OWNER-
5 SHIP OF ENERGY INFRASTRUCTURE IN IDAHO; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. LEGISLATIVE INTENT. It is the intent of the Legislature to
8 recognize the importance of maintaining local and regional control over
9 critical energy infrastructure. This section is intended to protect Idaho's
10 energy independence by preventing organizations created or controlled by
11 other state governments from owning, operating, or controlling Idaho elec-
12 trical transmission facilities.
13 SECTION 2. That Chapter 3, Title 61, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
14 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
15 ignated as Section 61-338, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
16 61-338. RESTRICTIONS ON OWNERSHIP OF ENERGY INFRASTRUCTURE IN
17 IDAHO. (1) No entity that was established, chartered, or primarily governed
18 by another state of the United States, or an agency thereof, shall acquire,
19 hold, or operate any ownership interest in Idaho's electrical transmission
20 facilities. This prohibition applies to transmission lines, substations,
21 and other related infrastructure that is directly involved in the interstate
22 or intrastate transmission of electricity.
23 (2) This section shall not:
24 (a) Apply to private entities, investor-owned utilities, cooperative
25 utilities, or independent transmission developers that are not di-
26 rectly created or controlled by another state government; or
27 (b) Prohibit Idaho-based utilities or businesses from entering
28 into contractual agreements for energy transmission services with
29 out-of-state entities.
30 (3) The Idaho public utilities commission shall have the authority to
31 review and authenticate the ownership of electrical transmission infra-
32 structure in Idaho to ensure compliance with this section.
33 (4) Any entity in violation of this section shall be required to divest
34 its interest in Idaho energy infrastructure within a period to be determined
35 by the commission but by no later than two (2) years from the effective date
36 of this section.
37 SECTION 3. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
38 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after its
39 passage and approval.

